wdi2-SH.STA.ODFC.ZS.def: People practicing open defecation refers to the percentage of the population defecating in the open, such as in fields, forest, bushes, open bodies of water, on beaches, in other open spaces or disposed of with solid waste.
wdi2-SH.STA.ODFC.ZS.name: People practicing open defecation
wdi2-SH.STA.ODFC.ZS.source: WHO/UNICEF Joint Monitoring Programme (JMP) for Water Supply and Sanitation (http://www.wssinfo.org/).
